cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of sequence-to-sequence models for natural language processing tasks, specifically machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of different layers at every step to adjust the amount of computation and model capacity, which falls under the category of machine learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses predicting the amount of computation required for a particular sequence, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Transformer models also suggests the category of neural networks (cs.NE) as a likely category. Finally, the paper uses the IWSLT German-English translation dataset, which is a natural language processing task involving image captioning, suggesting the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as a possible category.
